{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cb6c9e08-1382-4af8-83b4-d44e24d007b7","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pins the exception to the exact call\n- You can also inspect the exception (e.g., `ParamName`, `Message`)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3c0c6381-3be0-4885-bf15-fa7aa18382f9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no need to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":236,"requestId":"7C19:175BE3:27A9CB7:2BF6F77:69F946AF"},"id":"2df38084-cf3e-46a1-a8dd-d5b76d01c2d9","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:24:04.632Z","parentId":"786f2dad-21f5-4f9f-98d1-2efee97714ec"}
